Info: creates transcription factor binding motifs for the three NF-E2-like transcription factors, BACH1, BACH2, and NFE2
Disease: head and neck squamous cell carcinoma
General Info: While this site is mutated in several liver cancer patients, this specific G to A has only been described in 1 head and neck patient - in silico evidence suggests it creates new TFBS for three NF-E2-like transcription factors, BACH1, BACH2, and NFE2 but experimental evidence validating this and its role in cancer is lacking
FATHMM-MKL score predicts the mutation is not functionally significant
Not described in detail in paper - might need to dig through supplementary to find it
